gate: LOCKED
v:4 role:dev x:nextjs-tailwind
task: S03 T6 — #525 Phantom focusables: verify-first a11y check
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]
sprint: S03
repos: [crop-front]
branch: issue-525

context: |
  Original issue: mobile nav variants stay tabbable on desktop — 6-15 phantom focusables
  per page. Root cause was a flex w-0 h-0 lg:w-auto zero-size hide pattern.
  Audit update 2026-06-01: current layout/Header/Header.tsx uses hidden lg:flex / lg:hidden
  (display: none) at lines 67, 79, 101, 123, 131, 139 — display:none elements are NOT
  focusable by CSS spec. The w-0 h-0 pattern no longer exists.
  This is now verify-first. The phantoms may have been fixed incidentally in a header refactor,
  or they may still exist from nested components (Radix Sheet content, Suspense fallbacks).
  Do NOT write any fix code until prod evidence is posted.

steps:
  1. Branch: git checkout -b issue-525 dev
  2. Verify on prod — desktop (viewport 1280×800):
     a. Open https://crop.clintontractor.net/cart
     b. Run the verification snippet (from issue body):
        [...document.querySelectorAll('a, button, input, select, textarea, [tabindex]:not([tabindex="-1"]), [role="radio"]')]
          .filter(e => e.tabIndex >= 0)
          .filter(e => { const r = e.getBoundingClientRect(); return r.width === 0 && r.height === 0; })
          .map(e => ({ html: e.outerHTML.slice(0, 120), parent: e.parentElement?.className }))
     c. Repeat on /checkout/shipping and /parts
     d. Repeat on mobile viewport 375×667 (reverse direction check)
  3. Post findings as a comment on issue #525:
     - ZERO phantoms on all routes: close issue with evidence. Done.
     - PHANTOMS FOUND: for each element, expand snippet to also log:
         el.outerHTML.slice(0, 200) and el.closest('[class]').className
       Re-post detailed output identifying which component renders the phantom.
       Scope the fix to THAT component only (not the header globally).
  4. If phantoms found — fix:
     a. Identify the offending component from the snippet output.
     b. Apply appropriate hide: aria-hidden + tabIndex=-1 on focusable children, OR
        use Radix's correct Portal/inert pattern for Sheet content (MobileMenu).
     c. Add phantom-focusable assertion to existing a11y e2e (e2e-a11y-smoke):
        zero focusable elements with 0x0 bounding box on /cart, /checkout/shipping, /parts
        at both 1280x800 and 375x667. Cross-ref #679 (a11y umbrella).
     d. Commit: fix(a11y): eliminate phantom focusables in [component] (#525)
     e. Open draft PR into dev, reference #525, include before/after snippet output.

out:
  - issue #525 comment with prod findings (required)
  - fix only if phantoms confirmed (scope to identified component)
  - e2e test addition only if fix applied

done:
  - Prod verification performed on /cart, /checkout/shipping, /parts at 1280x800 + 375x667
  - Issue comment posted with evidence
  - EITHER: issue closed as fixed-by-refactor with evidence
  - OR: phantom elements identified → fix applied → snippet returns [] → PR merged
